.TH "SVGTextContentElement.getCharNumAtPosition" "JS" "January 2, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SVGTextContentElement.getCharNumAtPosition \- SVGTextContentElement:
getCharNumAtPosition() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getCharNumAtPosition()\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]SVGTextContentElement\f[R] interface represents the character
which caused a text glyph to be rendered at a given position in the
coordinate system.
Because the relationship between characters and glyphs is not
one\-to\-one, only the first character of the relevant typographic
character is returned.
.PP
If no character is found at the specified position, \f[CR]\-1\f[R] is
returned.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
SVGTextContentElement.getCharNumAtPosition(point)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]point\f[R]
An \f[CR]DOMPoint\f[R] object; the coordinates (x, y) where the position
of the character is to be checked in the user coordinate space.
.SS Return value
A long; the index of the character that corresponds to the position.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Finding the Character at a Specific Position
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]svg\f[R] width=\[dq]200\[dq] height=\[dq]100\[dq]>
  <\f[B]text\f[R] id=\[dq]exampleText\[dq] x=\[dq]10\[dq] y=\[dq]40\[dq] font\-size=\[dq]16\[dq]>Hello, SVG World!</\f[B]text\f[R]>
</\f[B]svg\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] textElement = document.getElementById(\[dq]exampleText\[dq]);

\f[I]// Create a DOMPoint for the position (30, 40)\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] point = \f[B]new\f[R] DOMPoint(30, 40);

\f[I]// Get the character at the specified position\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] charIndex = textElement.getCharNumAtPosition(point);

console.log(charIndex); \f[I]// Output: 2 (for character \[dq]l\[dq])\f[R]

\f[I]// Check with a point where no character is present\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] offPoint = \f[B]new\f[R] DOMPoint(300, 40);
\f[B]const\f[R] offCharIndex = textElement.getCharNumAtPosition(offPoint);

console.log(offCharIndex); \f[I]// Output: \-1 (no character found)\f[R]
.EE
